{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17514454","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17514454"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:22:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:22:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12318"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12318","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12318"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.03,0.27,0.68,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4839"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78070"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4839","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4839"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12318"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63492"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"496"},{"type":"tags","id":"1387"},{"type":"tags","id":"1444"},{"type":"tags","id":"4959"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9718"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7789"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7933"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26737"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44956"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78070","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78070"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old swimmer presents with a ten day history of pain in his right ear. The pain is aggravated by eating, chewing or the movement of the pinna and is now associated with mild unilateral deafness in that ear. He has had a discharge from the ear which was initially thin and clear but has now become yellowish and thick. On examination his right ear has thick, purulent discharge present in the external auditory canal and the meatal skin is inflamed, swollen and tender. The ear drum is not visible. There are no other abnormalities found inside the external auditory canal. His preauricular lymph nodes are enlarged and tender. Pure tone audiometry shows mild conductive deafness in the right ear and the left ear is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Furuncle","Otomycosis","Suppurative otitis media","Acute otitis externa","Bullous myringitis"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is a case of \u003Cstrong\u003Eacute otitis externa. \u003C/strong\u003EThis term describe the diffuse inflammation of the skin lining the external auditory canal, together with a mucopurulent discharge. The accumulation of discharge and epithelial debris in the auditory canal can lead to a mild conductive deafness. If it can be seen in these circumstances, the tympanic membrane will be oedematous and may have an underlying reactive effusion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA\u003Cstrong\u003E furuncle,\u003C/strong\u003E also known as a boil, is an acute staphylococcal infection of hair follicles which are present in the cartilaginous part of the external auditory canal. The patient presents first with itching followed by intense pain which is aggravated by the movement of the pinna or opening of the mouth. It can also result in conductive deafness because of the mechanical occlusion of the ear canal by the boil but it is usually associated with the presence of an obvious boil in the ear canal which can be noticed during an ear examination.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOtomycosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a fungal infection of the lining skin of the external auditory canal, common in tropical and subtropical climates in swimmers or patients with complaints of continuous ear discharge due to otitis media. Otomycosis also has a normal sized external auditory canal. In an acute otitis externa the external auditory canal is often swollen shut. The patient presents with itching and irritation in the ear, associated with conductive hearing loss sometimes. It is associated with the presence of a mass resembling a wet newspaper or blotting paper.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuppurative otitis media\u003C/strong\u003E is an infection of the middle ear cavity and can be associated with a perforated or congested tympanic membrane with a mucoid discharge of ear examination. It can be differentiated from acute otitis externa because pinnal movement causes minimal discomfort.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBullous myringitis\u003C/strong\u003E also known as otitis externa haemorrhagica is an inflammatory condition of the tympanic membrane and is associated with the presence of blebs, swelling and redness of the tympanic membrane.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diffuse otitis externa is an inflammatory condition of the lining skin of the external auditory canal.","Pain aggravated by movement of the pinna is a characteristic feature of otitis externa."],"references":["Wiegand S, Berner R, Schneider A, Lundershausen E, Dietz A. Otitis Externa. Dtsch Arztebl Int. 2019 Mar 29;116(13):224-234. doi: 10.3238/arztebl.2019.0224. PMID: 31064650; PMCID: PMC6522672. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31064650/","Medina-Blasini Y, Sharman T. Otitis Externa. 2023 Jul 31. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32310515. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32310515/","Jackson EA, Geer K. Acute Otitis Externa: Rapid Evidence Review. Am Fam Physician. 2023 Feb;107(2):145-151. PMID: 36791445. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36791445/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63492"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12318"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63492","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63492"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-09T12:47:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-09T12:48:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4839"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78070"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/35"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc43","name":"Otorhinolaryngology","synonyms":["ENT","HEENT"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:40:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating m